    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>More Gun Control Isn't Answer to Shooting</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Fadi Zanayed letter responds to Feb 25 editorial on shooting at Empire State Building</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Feb. 25 editorial on the shooting at the Empire State Building calls for Federal standards that should be met before a gun can be purchased.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your Feb. 25 editorial on the shooting at the Empire State Building calls for Federal standards that should be met before a gun can be purchased.</p>
        <p>You suggest that a utility bill or rent bill should be used to demonstrate that the applicant has been at his address for at least three months. But that is not sufficient. Millions of nonresident aliens who have utility bills fill our cities and communities.</p>
        <p>Instead, the requirement should be proof of citizenship (voter registration) or legal residency (green card). Taking into account that not every citizen is a registered voter, those who want to purchase a gun should take on the civic burden of registering to vote.</p>
        <p>FADI ZANAYED  Chicago, Feb. 25, 1997</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
